{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843481835,"sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","part":{"id":"prt_d78850f76001Sk1RKYE1e9U1L0","messageID":"msg_d788502fd001aQ5g1kdR1SeUSC","sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7b9e75a779e049aaa77aa8d8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-005\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n18: \n19: ### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource in namespace \"default\" with valid TargetPorts and PodTemplate\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the AgentRuntime specification\n24: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod matching the PodTemplate specification\n25: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent AgentRuntime\n26: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n27: \n28: ### AR-005-002: Create Sandbox from CodeInterpreter\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource in namespace \"default\" with valid Template configuration\n31: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n32: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the CodeInterpreter template specification\n33: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod using the ContainerTemplateSpec\n34: - **AND** SHALL apply warm pool logic if WarmPoolSize > 0\n35: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent CodeInterpreter\n36: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n37: \n38: ### AR-005-003: Sandbox creation with custom parameters\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource\n41: - **WHEN** a POST request includes custom override parameters in the request body\n42: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the overrides to the sandbox specification\n43: - **AND** SHALL validate that override values meet validation constraints\n44: - **AND** SHALL merge overrides with the base template\n45: \n46: ### AR-005-004: Sandbox creation validation failure\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with invalid PodTemplate (e.g., missing required container image)\n49: - **WHEN** a POST request attempts to create a sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n51: - **AND** SHALL include validation error details in the response\n52: \n53: ### AR-005-005: Sandbox creation for non-existent resource\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n56: - **WHEN** a POST request targets a non-existent AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n57: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Scenario: Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n62: \n63: ### AR-005-010: Get Sandbox Status\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active sandboxes\n66: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n67: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return the current sandbox status including:\n68:   - Pod phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n69:   - Container states\n70:   - IP address if assigned\n71:   - Creation timestamp\n72:   - Parent resource reference (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\n73: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n74: \n75: ### AR-005-011: List Sandboxes\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances running in a namespace\n78: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes`\n79: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a list of all sandboxes in the namespace\n80: - **AND** SHALL support labelSelector query parameter for filtering\n81: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata and status summary\n82: \n83: ### AR-005-012: Delete Sandbox\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox instance\n86: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n87: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate the sandbox Pod\n88: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n89: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n90: \n91: ### AR-005-013: Delete Sandbox with force option\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully\n94: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n95: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully terminate the sandbox\n96: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n97: \n98: ### AR-005-014: Watch Sandboxes\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances\n101: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?watch=true`\n102: - **THEN** the server SHALL stream sandbox events as NDJSON\n103: - **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as sandboxes change state\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Scenario: Sandbox Template Processing\n108: \n109: ### AR-005-020: Process AgentRuntime PodTemplate\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a PodTemplate containing custom containers, volumes, and node selectors\n112: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this AgentRuntime\n113: - **THEN** the handler SHALL merge the PodTemplate.Spec with default values\n114: - **AND** SHALL apply the specified NodeSelector, Affinity, and Tolerations\n115: - **AND** SHALL preserve InitContainers if specified\n116: \n117: ### AR-005-021: Process CodeInterpreter ContainerTemplate\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a ContainerTemplate (image, command, args, env, resources)\n120: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this CodeInterpreter\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Pod with a single container from the template\n122: - **AND** SHALL apply resource requirements from the template\n123: - **AND** SHALL set the RuntimeClassName if specified\n124: \n125: ### AR-005-022: Apply Security Context\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with SecurityContext configured\n128: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply PodSecurityContext to the Pod\n130: - **AND** SHALL apply SecurityContext to each container\n131: - **AND** SHALL validate security context values against policy\n132: \n133: ### AR-005-023: Inject Environment Variables\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with Env variables in the template\n136: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n137: - **THEN** the handler SHALL inject the specified environment variables\n138: - **AND** SHALL support both static values and references (e.g., from secrets, configmaps)\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Sandbox Pool Management\n143: \n144: ### AR-005-030: Warm Pool Pre-provisioning\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize = 3\n147: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is created or becomes ready\n148: - **THEN** the handler SHALL proactively create 3 sandbox Pods\n149: - **AND** SHALL mark them as warm/ready\n150: - **AND** SHALL maintain the warm pool size\n151: \n152: ### AR-005-031: Warm Pool Scaling\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** a warm pool with 3 ready sandboxes\n155: - **WHEN** a new sandbox request arrives and all warm sandboxes are in use\n156: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create an additional sandbox to handle the request\n157: - **AND** SHALL attempt to maintain the warm pool size\n158: \n159: ### AR-005-032: Warm Pool Cleanup\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize reduced from 5 to 2\n162: - **WHEN** the pool size change is detected\n163: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate excess warm sandboxes\n164: - **AND** SHALL gracefully drain unused sandboxes first\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Scenario: Sandbox Networking\n169: \n170: ### AR-005-040: Expose Sandbox Ports\n171: \n172: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts configured (port 8080, protocol HTTP)\n173: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n174: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Service exposing the specified ports\n175: - **AND** SHALL set up appropriate network policies if configured\n176: - **AND** SHALL configure ingress routing based on PathPrefix\n177: \n178: ### AR-005-041: Sandbox Ingress Configuration\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts including PathPrefix \"/api\"\n181: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n182: - **THEN** the handler SHALL configure ingress rules for the specified path\n183: - **AND** SHALL ensure the path prefix is routed to the correct container port\n184: \n185: ### AR-005-042: Network Policy Enforcement\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with network policy requirements\n188: - **WHEN** creating network resources\n189: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply NetworkPolicy resources to restrict traffic\n190: - **AND** SHALL support both ingress and egress rules\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Scenario: Sandbox Scheduling\n195: \n196: ### AR-005-050: Node Selection\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with NodeSelector configured (disktype=ssd, region=us-west)\n199: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n200: - **THEN** the handler SHALL schedule the Pod on a node matching the node selectors\n201: - **AND** SHALL handle scheduling failures gracefully\n202: \n203: ### AR-005-051: Affinity and Anti-Affinity\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Affinity rules (podAntiAffinity, nodeAffinity)\n206: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n207: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the affinity rules to Pod scheduling\n208: - **AND** SHALL respect both required and preferred affinity rules\n209: \n210: ### AR-005-052: Resource Quota Enforcement\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** a namespace with ResourceQuota limiting CPU, memory, or pod count\n213: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox exceeds quota\n214: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n215: - **AND** SHALL include quota violation details in the response\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Scenario: Error Handling and Recovery\n220: \n221: ### AR-005-060: Pod Creation Failure\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request\n224: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during Pod creation\n225: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code (4xx or 5xx)\n226: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n227: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n228: \n229: ### AR-005-061: Sandbox Status Sync\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod has crashed or been killed externally\n232: - **WHEN** querying sandbox status\n233: - **THEN** the handler SHALL detect the stale state\n234: - **AND** SHALL update the sandbox status to reflect the actual Pod state\n235: - **AND** SHALL emit events for status changes\n236: \n237: ### AR-005-062: Graceful Shutdown\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox\n240: - **WHEN** the WorkloadManager receives shutdown signal\n241: - **THEN** the handler SHALL not accept new sandbox requests\n242: - **AND** SHALL wait for in-flight sandbox creations to complete\n243: - **AND** SHALL not terminate existing sandboxes (responsibility of controller)\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## References\n248: \n249: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n250: - Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n251: - AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n252: - CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n253: - client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n254: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 254 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-005\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n\n### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843481807,"end":1775843481833}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843481840,"sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","part":{"id":"prt_d78851432001bInvh6y4ruwHpA","messageID":"msg_d788502fd001aQ5g1kdR1SeUSC","sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f31f098e056435db778dec3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Core Handlers\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Add `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `SandboxEntryPoint` types with Validate() method\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Constants: DefaultSandboxTTL, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout, label/annotation keys (SessionID, WorkloadName, SandboxName, IdleTimeout)\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` - GVR variables (SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR), Informers struct, Start() and WaitForCacheSync() methods\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` - SandboxReconciler struct, WatchSandboxOnce() returning channel, getSandboxStatus()\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` - K8sClient struct with dynamic client, informer factory, listers; ClientCache for per-user clients; GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()\n17: - [ ] **1.6** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleAgentRuntimeCreate() handler function\n18: - [ ] **1.7** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleCodeInterpreterCreate() handler function\n19: - [ ] **1.8** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Register new routes POST /v1/agent-runtime, POST /v1/code-interpreter\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Phase 2: Workload Builder\n24: \n25: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` - buildSandboxObject() converting AgentRuntime to Sandbox unstructured object\n26: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` - buildSandboxClaimObject() for WarmPool path\n27: - [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` - buildEntryPoints() to construct SandboxEntryPoint array from podIP and TargetPorts\n28: - [ ] **2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` - resolvePodIP() with annotation, lister, and ownerReference fallback logic\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## Phase 3: Sandbox Creator\n33: \n34: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` - sandboxCreator struct with k8sClient, sandboxController, storeClient, publicKey fields\n35: - [ ] **3.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` - createSandbox() method implementing full flow (watcher registration → store placeholder → CR create → wait running → resolve IP → store update)\n36: - [ ] **3.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` - rollback logic for CR deletion and store cleanup on timeout/failure\n37: - [ ] **3.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` - Handle WarmPoolSize > 0 path (create SandboxClaim vs Sandbox)\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Phase 4: Auth & GC\n42: \n43: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go` - authMiddleware with token validation, context keys (userToken, serviceAccount, serviceAccountName, namespace)\n44: - [ ] **4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go` - validateServiceAccountToken() using TokenReview API\n45: - [ ] **4.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - garbageCollector struct with store client and k8sClient\n46: - [ ] **4.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - gcLoop() for periodic cleanup of expired sandboxes\n47: - [ ] **4.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - cleanupExpiredSandboxes() with 2-minute tick interval\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Phase 5: Error Handling\n52: \n53: - [ ] **5.1** Implement error types: ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound, ErrTemplateMissing\n54: - [ ] **5.2** Map error types to HTTP status codes in handlers (400 for validation, 401 for auth, 404 for not found, 500 for internal)\n55: - [ ] **5.3** Add error response DTOs in types.go (ErrorResponse with Message field)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Phase 6: Integration Points\n60: \n61: - [ ] **6.1** Integrate with client-go: import AgentRuntimeInterface, CodeInterpreterInterface, SharedInformerFactory\n62: - [ ] **6.2** Integrate with Store: call StoreSandbox(), UpdateSandbox(), DeleteSandboxBySessionID()\n63: - [ ] **6.3** Integrate with SandboxReconciler: call WatchSandboxOnce() for status waiting\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Phase 7: Unit Tests\n68: \n69: - [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` - TestBuildSandboxObject_ValidRuntime\n70: - [ ] **7.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` - TestBuildSandboxClaimObject_WarmPool\n71: - [ ] **7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` - TestBuildEntryPoints_DefaultPorts\n72: - [ ] **7.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` - TestResolvePodIP_FromAnnotation\n73: - [ ] **7.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` - TestResolvePodIP_FromOwnerReference\n74: - [ ] **7.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` - TestCreateSandbox_Success\n75: - [ ] **7.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` - TestCreateSandbox_Timeout\n76: - [ ] **7.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` - TestCreateSandbox_RollbackOnFailure\n77: - [ ] **7.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` - TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success\n78: - [ ] **7.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` - TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate\n79: - [ ] **7.11** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` - TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_WarmPool\n80: - [ ] **7.12** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` - TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD\n81: - [ ] **7.13** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go` - TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate table-driven tests\n82: - [ ] **7.14** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/auth_test.go` - TestAuthMiddleware_ValidToken\n83: - [ ] **7.15** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/auth_test.go` - TestAuthMiddleware_MissingToken\n84: - [ ] **7.16** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - TestGarbageCollector_ExpiredSandbox\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## Phase 8: Integration Tests\n89: \n90: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` - E2E test with real K8s cluster (TestE2E_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox)\n91: - [ ] **8.2** Test warm pool pre-provisioning with CodeInterpreter WarmPoolSize > 0\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Phase 9: Verification\n96: \n97: - [ ] **9.1** Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - successful compilation\n98: - [ ] **9.2** Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - all unit tests pass\n99: - [ ] **9.3** Run `go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no race conditions\n100: - [ ] **9.4** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no issues\n101: - [ ] **9.5** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - linter passes\n102: - [ ] **9.6** Verify test coverage > 40% with `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Dependencies\n107: \n108: | Task | Depends On |\n109: |------|------------|\n110: | Phase 1 | AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library |\n111: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 (types, defaults, informers) |\n112: | Phase 3 | Phase 1 + Phase 2 |\n113: | Phase 4 | Phase 1 (k8s_client) |\n114: | Phase 5 | Phase 1 (types) |\n115: | Phase 6 | client-go, store package, SandboxReconciler |\n116: | Phase 7 | Phase 1-5 (implementation complete) |\n117: | Phase 8 | Phase 7 (unit tests) |\n118: | Phase 9 | All phases |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## References\n123: \n124: - Design: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md`\n125: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n126: - Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Core Handlers\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Add `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `SandboxEntryPoint` types with Validate() method\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Constants: DefaultSandboxTTL, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout, label/annotation keys (SessionID, WorkloadName, SandboxName, IdleTimeout)\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` - GVR variables (SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR), Informers struct, Start() and WaitForCacheSync() methods\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` - SandboxReconciler struct, WatchSandboxOnce() returning channel, getSandboxStatus()\n- [ ] **1.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` - K8sClient struct with dynamic client, informer factory, listers; ClientCache for per-user clients; GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()\n- [ ] **1.6** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleAgentRuntimeCreate() handler function\n- [ ] **1.7** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleCodeInterpreterCreate() handler function\n- [ ] **1.8** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Register new routes POST /v1/agent-runtime, POST /v1/code-interpreter\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775843481810,"end":1775843481837}}}}
