{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775843500325,"sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","part":{"id":"prt_d78856121001WcmEZEbpWr6Mvf","messageID":"msg_d788552af0012jexFoU8KQZLVV","sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843547153,"sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","part":{"id":"prt_d788573a8001aUpFlsQ5UKooH2","messageID":"msg_d788552af0012jexFoU8KQZLVV","sessionID":"ses_2877b1772ffeiGgFV0JJ2qd1m4","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_4feb238580cc46a39c49a25f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-006\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n\n### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known SessionID\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by SessionID\n- **AND** SHALL initiate Pod termination\n- **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n- **AND** SHALL remove the sandbox from the store\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n\n### AR-006-002: Delete Sandbox by Name\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known name\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by name\n- **AND** SHALL perform the same cleanup as AR-006-001\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n\n### AR-006-003: Force Delete Sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully (stuck in Terminating state > 5 minutes)\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully delete the Pod using DeleteOptions\n- **AND** SHALL bypass finalizers if necessary\n- **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n\n### AR-006-004: Delete Non-existent Sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request targets a non-existent sandbox\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n- **AND** SHALL include error message \"sandbox not found\"\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Graceful Shutdown\n\n### AR-006-010: Graceful Termination with Draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a running sandbox with active connections\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is received with `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL send SIGTERM to the sandbox process\n- **AND** SHALL wait for grace period before force termination\n- **AND** SHALL allow in-flight requests to complete\n- **AND** SHALL reject new requests during grace period\n- **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK only after termination completes or grace period expires\n\n### AR-006-011: Pre-delete Hook\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with pre-delete lifecycle hook configured\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is received\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL execute the pre-delete hook\n- **AND** SHALL wait for hook to complete (max 30 seconds)\n- **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of hook result\n- **AND** SHALL log hook execution status\n\n### AR-006-012: Connection Draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with active connections\n- **WHEN** graceful termination is initiated\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL stop routing new traffic to the sandbox\n- **AND** SHALL wait for existing connections to close (max grace period)\n- **AND** SHALL return \"draining\" status during the grace period\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: TTL and Expiration\n\n### AR-006-020: Sandbox TTL Enforcement\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with TTL set to 1 hour\n- **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds its TTL\n- **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL automatically delete the sandbox\n- **AND** SHALL emit an event for TTL expiration\n- **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n- **AND** SHALL log the expiration for auditing\n\n### AR-006-021: Idle Timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with IdleTimeout set to 10 minutes\n- **WHEN** no requests are received for 10 minutes\n- **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL mark the sandbox as idle\n- **AND** SHALL terminate idle sandboxes based on idle timeout policy\n- **AND** SHALL support both immediate deletion and graceful draining for idle sandboxes\n\n### AR-006-022: Max Lifetime\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with MaxLifetime set to 24 hours\n- **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds MaxLifetime\n- **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL reject new requests\n- **AND** SHALL terminate the sandbox after current requests complete\n- **AND** SHALL ensure sandboxes do not run indefinitely\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Batch Operations\n\n### AR-006-030: Delete All Sandboxes in Namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances in a namespace\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` with `deleteAll=true`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all sandboxes in the namespace\n- **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n- **AND** SHALL support async deletion for large batches\n\n### AR-006-031: Delete Sandboxes by Label Selector\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances with various labels\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `labelSelector=app=foo`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL delete only sandboxes matching the label selector\n- **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n\n### AR-006-032: Delete Stale Sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** sandboxes in \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" state for > 1 hour\n- **WHEN** the garbage collector runs\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL identify stale sandboxes\n- **AND** SHALL automatically clean up stale sandboxes\n- **AND** SHALL emit events for stale sandbox cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Lifecycle Events\n\n### AR-006-040: Emit Deletion Event\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event\n- **AND** SHALL include deletion reason, initiated by, and timestamp\n\n### AR-006-041: Webhook Notification on Deletion\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with deletion webhook configured\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL send POST notification to the webhook URL\n- **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata in the request body\n- **AND** SHALL retry up to 3 times on failure\n- **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of webhook response\n\n### AR-006-042: Deletion Audit Log\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion operation\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL log:\n  - Sandbox identifier (SessionID, name)\n  - Namespace\n  - Deletion reason (explicit, TTL, idle, stale)\n  - Initiator (user, system)\n  - Duration from deletion request to completion\n  - Resources cleaned up\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Resource Cleanup\n\n### AR-006-050: Cleanup Associated Services\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with associated Services\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all Services owned by the sandbox\n- **AND** SHALL use ownerReference for automatic cleanup verification\n\n### AR-006-051: Cleanup ConfigMaps and Secrets\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with injected ConfigMaps or Secrets\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL delete ConfigMaps if marked for deletion\n- **AND** SHALL NOT delete Secrets (they may be shared)\n- **AND** SHALL log cleanup actions\n\n### AR-006-052: Cleanup PVCs\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with PVCs\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL handle PVC cleanup based on ReclaimPolicy\n- **AND** SHALL delete PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Delete\n- **AND** SHALL retain PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Error Handling\n\n### AR-006-060: Deletion Failure Handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion request\n- **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during deletion\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code\n- **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n- **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n- **AND** SHALL retry deletion up to 3 times for transient errors\n\n### AR-006-061: Orphaned Resource Cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod was deleted externally\n- **WHEN** the garbage collector detects the orphan\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL clean up the sandbox record\n- **AND** SHALL clean up any orphaned Services or ConfigMaps\n- **AND** SHALL emit an event for orphan cleanup\n\n### AR-006-062: Finalizer Handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with finalizers\n- **WHEN** deletion is requested\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL execute all finalizers\n- **AND** SHALL remove finalizer only after successful execution\n- **AND** SHALL handle stuck finalizers with force deletion\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n- Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n- Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- Garbage Collector: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843547138,"end":1775843547149}}}}
